==Translingual==

===Etymology===
Acronym from English [[LOL]] for "laughing out loud", "lots of love" or "lots of laughs", it can also mean 'laugh out load' or even 'lovin of love' lol is all about internet quick chat. you use it on internet talk spots eg: myspace and hotmail. lol is a way to skip out typing in the word 'very funny' or 'haha, it is a slang also used now in streets and day to day talking,. so have a lolllage day matees...

===Interjection===
'''LOL'''

# {{context|internet slang|Text messaging}} Used to express [[laughter]], literally "Laughing Out Loud".
# {{context|rare}} "Lots Of Love".

